hysical implications of quantum theory suggest that scientific knowledge will never truly describe mind-independent reality, the notion of such an ultimate reality--one we can never access directly or rationally and which he calls "veiled reality"--remains conceptually necessary nonetheless.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aPhysicsxPhilosophy. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Quantum Theory.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691240237zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691240237423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691240237/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK